      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Power Block Structure</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">One power block consists
of one or two power modules (maximum 25 kVA).<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Up to four power blocks can be paralleled (maximum 100 kVA)</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Each power block has its own controller (maximum four controllers)<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Data collection, communication, load sharing and parallel behavior
is controlled by the master controller</p>
                        </li>
                     </ul>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Inverter self-test is run at every start-up</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Odd number of power modules is allowed</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </p>
